HEADWORD: Longshoreman
<hw>Long"shore`man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Longshoremen</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Abbrev. fr.
<ets>alongshoreman</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of a class of laborers
employed about the wharves of a seaport, especially in loading and
unloading vessels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

